item.description:
big data The idea that large databases of seemingly random data (ex. purchasing habits, location information) about people are valueable.
block size The POSIX standard defines a block size of 512 bytes. However, this size is harder to read, so by default, the df and du output in most Linux distributions is in 1024-byte blocks.
caching means that data likely to be used in the future is kept &ldquo;nearby&rdquo;
